pullrequest.title: [A-1] Performance test for the level manager

content.raw: Yes, this is caused by `<plugin name="ignition::gazebo" filename="dummy">` in the SDF file. It's trying to load `dummy` which doesn't exist. We are abusing the plugin tag to put configurations options for ign-gazebo in there, but the `filename` attribute is required and I just put `dummy` there as a place holder. We could check if if the plugin name is `ignition::gazebo` and not try to load the plugin, but I thought this will be addressed more fully when we added extensions to SDF.

We could check if if the plugin name is ignition::gazebo and not try to load the plugin, but I thought this will be addressed more fully when we added extensions to SDF.
